data.title: Can't wait to return
data.text:
We were looking for a different restaurant, which we didn't find, so this was originally not our first choice. We were there early so we were deceived by the small number of patrons when we first arrived. And it was a great surprise. We will return as soon as possible! We ate beef with broccoli, pork fried rice, and sesame chicken; we didn't all agree on which dish was the favorite, but we did agree it was the best 
Chinese food we'd had in a long time.

data.title: Excellent authentic Cantonese cuisine
data.text: Davis is fortunate to have an authentic Cantonese restaurant in town finally. Cantonese is the most popular of all Chinese cuisines.  The menu is extensive with color photos.  This restaurant serves Chinese food, not Chinese-American food! The premises are clean; staff are young and service-oriented.  Dishes can be tweaked to accommodate individual preferences.  flavors are spot on and delicious. Families and groups are welcome.

data.title: Chef special is a great start...
data.text: This is Davis' newest Chinese restaurant. They completely re-did the decor and with the  corner location it shows well.  Really liked the booth seating.  I ordered the Chef's Seafood Special that was the best.  The portions are huge, so splitting an entree is not a problem for most couples. the place was packed for a Wednesday night. Be patient if the restaurant is busy as the kitchen is try its best to keep up.

data.title: Cant I give more than 5 "stars"
data.text: The food at this place is exceptional. I've been here four times in the last week. Every time I've tried something completely different and have been surprised and delighted by all my choices. Without question my current favorite is salt-and-pepper fish.

data.title: Davis' newest Chinese restaurant is a hit...
data.text: Formerly known as the Silver Dragon. The new owners promised a unique Szechuan  dining experience.  They have delivered on this by adding new decor to the dining room and a new menu. The staff sat us quickly and took out drink order immediately.  The restaurant was very busy for a Sunday evening, so the order took a while.  The food was delicious; we ordered the House Special, Seafood Combo.  This order could easily feed two. The waitress told us, "All the entrees can feed two."  Ours was squid, shrimp and scallops with bok choy and mushrooms in a light brown gravy served in a pot. Funny story, when I ordered the meal, the waitress repeated, "Ok house special seafood combo. Do you want meat?  I said, no. She repeated, seafood combo, no meat. I said yes no meat.  Apparently you can add meat to a seafood combo.  Only bummer was we never saw our waitress until after the meal. This place was busy, so it has to be good and it was.
